Absolutely not.  But morality isn't factual, it isn't based on facts, it's based on opinions.  I fail to see the correlation.<br>
<br>
You cannot factually say that ANYTHING is immoral.  It's based on beliefs.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Absolute moralities requires a creator.  Since there are no facts that prove a creator, and since said creator is different across multiple cultures and beliefs.  How can morality be absolute??  <br>
<br>
How about this example as a compromise...<br>
<br>
If there is a creator, then there is an absolute moral structure.  It is left to us to find our own morality based on what we believe the creator has defined. (or not defined)  When we die, we find out if there ever was an absolute moral code, and we find out whether our interpretation of it was correct.  While we live, we live our lives by our own OPINIONS of what that moral code should be. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wolvar>Wolvar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/7/03 12:58:08 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elcheproudfoot>Elche Proudfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mmmmm lobster</span><br>  Posts: 1096<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/03 1:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=448.topic&index=194>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.woc.org/public/oneirodynia/images/srllogo.GIF height=180 width=180></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Morality is not relative.&quot;</span><hr size=1> Was killing the indians and taking their land immoral.  -- inalienable right to life,property<br>
