&quot;Did morale change over time ?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Perception</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of morality changes over time.  This is why one cannot judge too harshly men like Southern generals in the civil war.  One cannot impose the moral clarity of the present on the past.  But just because they <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>believed</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> it wasn't wrong, doesn't mean it that they were right.  This is not a terribly difficult concept to grasp.  <br>
<br>
Elche and I differ on (at least) one point - I believe it is possible to know the True and Absolute morality, because I believe it is explained to us by our Creator.  Elche strikes me as more of a Deist, but that's fine.  But regardless of whether you believe that the Truth is knowable or not, the fact remains that humans, and society in general, can be closer or farther away from that knowledge at different periods in its history.  Ignorance of the truth does not excuse, but it does explain. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.visveres.myguilds.com/sigs/caledhon.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wolvar>Wolvar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>My third character is Lovawr</span><br>  Posts: 1737<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/03 1:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=448.topic&index=201>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Morality is not relative.&quot;</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
